{
  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_6' aria-label=\" State of Haryana & Others versus Aalamgir & Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('6','2025','2025_3_1460_1481','2025INSC407'); ><font size='4'> <strong>STATE OF HARYANA & OTHERS<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>AALAMGIR & OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 3 S.C.R. 1460</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 407</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004742025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : B.V. NAGARATHNA, SATISH CHANDRA SHARMA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The present appeals assail the orders passed by the Punjab and Haryana High Court in several writ petitions in respect of acquisition of various parcels of land from time to time by issuance of notifications u/ss.4 and 6 of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894. Headnotes&dagger; &ndash; ss.4 and 6 &ndash; Right to Fair Compensation and Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and Resettlement Act, 2013 &ndash; s.24(2) &ndash; The respondents land owners/subsequent purchasers have assailed the acquisition process &ndash; The validity of the acquisition were<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 18-03-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 4052/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('6','2025','2025_3_1460_1481','2025INSC407','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('6','2025','2025